section.section:
State money provided under this section may not be used:
for administrative costs;
for compensation or fringe benefits to employees or members of county governments, or fire, rescue, or ambulance companies;
for travel or meal expenses;
for fuel, utility, or routine maintenance costs of facilities or equipment;
to acquire new or replacement fire hydrants, water mains, or emergency alarm systems not installed at a fire, rescue, or ambulance facility;
for insurance;
for fund-raising activities;
to refinance debt or another obligation incurred before July 1, 1985;
to replace or repair eligible items to the extent that insurance proceeds are available;
for costs associated with the "9-1-1" emergency telephone system; or
for land or interests in land.
